webpackJsonp([0xa2aa8e615bad],{510:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{githubRepo:"https://github.com/esttorhe/esttorhe.github.io",author:"Esteban Torres"}},markdownRemark:{frontmatter:{title:"#21DaysChallenge",issueNumber:19,categories:["personal","lifestyle"],tags:["diet","fitness","exercise"],author:null,date:"2015-07-30T20:05:26.000Z"},html:'<p>Is a Â«well knownÂ» fact that I\'m trying to get to 12% body fat; last year I was really close at 14% but then I ricocheted back to 17% and my mental state took a toll and was not able to get back on track. I\'ve been going up &#x26; down on my body fat since then.</p>\n<p>Last December I hit horrible numbers because I pretty much gave up on exercising ðŸ’ª and dieting ðŸŒ¿ Â¯\\_(ãƒ„)_/Â¯</p>\n<!--more-->\n<p>Then I wrote <a href="http://estebantorr.es/blog/2014/12/31/new-year-resolutions/">this article</a> about my resolutions for 2015 ðŸŽ‰ and here\'s an almost up to date <a href="https://github.com/esttorhe/2015-Resolutions">repo</a> where I\'m keeping track of my accomplishments.</p>\n<p>As you can see I\'m going pretty well with my resolutions (as soon as I publish this post I\'ll hit the mark at 500 public contributions ðŸŽ‰) but I\'m kind stumbling with my fitness goal.</p>\n<p>Â«InspiredÂ» (for a lack of a better word) by <a href="https://www.facebook.com/MissAmandaCerny/photos/a.131955946897595.28409.100344450058745/868664193226763/">Amanda Cerny\'s 21 day gym challenge</a> I decided to do the same to try and get back on the fitness ðŸšƒ</p>\n<h2 id="the-theory"><a href="#the-theory" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>The theory</h2>\n<p>All this <code class="language-text">21 days</code> challenge is because <a href="http://www.quora.com/Does-it-really-take-21-days-to-break-a-habit">there\'s a theory</a> that states that 21 days is how long it takes to make or brake a habit.</p>\n<p>Perhaps its true, maybe not; but I\'ve found that some consistency does help me get back to a mindset when I\'m not motivated enough.</p>\n<h2 id="thats-it"><a href="#thats-it" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>That\'s it</h2>\n<p>And basically that\'s it; I\'m trying to go 21 days doing exercise and following my diet exactly, letter by letter to try and get back on track.</p>\n<p>I created a repo where I\'m going to be tracking each day and wether or not I did exercised or followed my diet.</p>\n<p><a href="https://github.com/esttorhe/21DaysChallenge">21 Days Repo</a></p>\n<hr>\n<p><em>Note: worth noting that my gym doesn\'t open on Sundays; which means that maybe I won\'t workout on Sundays and just don\'t count that day or maybe I\'ll just jog 15 minutes or so; haven\'t decided yet.</em></p>',url:"21DaysChallenge"}},pathContext:{id:"/home/travis/build/esttorhe/esttorhe.github.io/content/_posts/2015-07-30-21DaysChallenge.markdown absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark"}}}});
